{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "A Good Name"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A good name is more desirable than great riches; favor is better than silver and gold."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The rich and the poor have this in common: The LORD is Maker of them all."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The prudent see danger and take cover, but the simple keep going and suffer the consequences."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The rewards of humility and the fear of the LORDare wealth and honor and life."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Thorns and snares lie on the path of the perverse; he who guards his soul stays far from them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Train up a child in the way he should go, and when he is old he will not depart from it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The rich rule over the poor, and the borrower is slave to the lender."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who sows injustice will reap disaster, and the rod of his fury will be destroyed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A generous man will be blessed, for he shares his bread with the poor."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Drive out the mocker, and conflict will depart; even quarreling and insults will cease."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who loves a pure heart and gracious lipswill have the king for a friend."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The LORD’s eyes keep watch over knowledge, but He frustrates the words of the faithless."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The slacker says,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "There is a lion outside! I will be slain in the streets!",
          "speaker": "The slacker"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The mouth of an adulteress is a deep pit; he who is under the wrath of the LORD will fall into it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Foolishness is bound up in the heart of a child, but the rod of discipline drives it far from him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Oppressing the poor to enrich oneself or giving gifts to the richwill surely lead to poverty."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Thirty Sayings of the Wise"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 1"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Incline your ear and hear the words of the wise—apply your mind to my knowledge—"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for it is pleasing when you keep them within you and they are constantly on your lips."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "So that your trust may be in the LORD, I instruct you today—yes, you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Have I not written for you thirty sayings about counsel and knowledge,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "to show you true and reliable words, that you may soundly answer those who sent you?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 2"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not rob a poor man because he is poor, and do not crush the afflicted at the gate,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for the LORD will take up their case and will plunder those who rob them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 3"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not make friends with an angry man, and do not associate with a hot-tempered man,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "or you may learn his ways and entangle yourself in a snare."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 4"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not be one who gives pledges, who puts up security for debts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If you have nothing with which to pay, why should your bed be taken from under you?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 5"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not move an ancient boundary stone which your fathers have placed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Saying 6"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do you see a man skilled in his work? He will be stationed in the presence of kings;\nhe will not st and before obscure men."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}